&reftitle.description;
public static intnullIntlChar::getBlockCode intstringcodepoint
Returns the Unicode allocation block that contains the character.

&reftitle.returnvalues;


 Returns the block value for codepoint.
 See the IntlChar::BLOCK_CODE_* constants for possible return values. Returns &null; on failure.

  &reftitle.examples;

   &intl.codepoint.example;


<?php
var_dump(IntlChar::getBlockCode("A") === IntlChar::BLOCK_CODE_BASIC_LATIN);
var_dump(IntlChar::getBlockCode("Î¦") === IntlChar::BLOCK_CODE_GREEK);
var_dump(IntlChar::getBlockCode("\u{2603}") === IntlChar::BLOCK_CODE_MISCELLANEOUS_SYMBOLS);
?>


   &example.outputs;


bool(true)
bool(true)
bool(true)
